Description: This registry defines messages for representing Ami Node Manager Oem errors in Redfish

AlertThresholdPowerBudgetOutOfRange.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because either Alert Threshold is Out of Range Or Power budget is out of Range.
AlertThresholdPowerBudgetOutOfRange.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because either Alert Threshold is Out of Range Or Power budget is out of Range. IPMI Error Code is %1.
AlertThresholdPowerBudgetOutOfRange.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

CorrectionTimeOutOfRange.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Correction time is Out of Range.
CorrectionTimeOutOfRange.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Correction time is Out of Range. IPMI Error Code is %1.
CorrectionTimeOutOfRange.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

IncompatibleState.Description: Cannot execute command. Command, or request parameter(s), not supported in present state of Node Manager Service.
IncompatibleState.Message: The request could not be completed because a command or request parameter is not supported in the present state of Node Manager Service. IPMI Error Code is %1.
IncompatibleState.Resolution: Verify that the Node Manager Service is not in a conflicting state and resubmit the request.

InsufficientPrivilegeLevel.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because of Insufficient Privilege Level.
InsufficientPrivilegeLevel.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because of Insufficient Privilege Level. IPMI Error Code is %1.
InsufficientPrivilegeLevel.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

InvalidAggressiveCPUPowerCorrectionExcep.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because either invalid value passed for Aggressive CPU Power Correction field or Exception Action is invalid for given policy type.
InvalidAggressiveCPUPowerCorrectionExcep.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because invalid value for Aggressive CPU Power correction field or Exception Action is invalid for given policy type. IPMI Error Code is %1.
InvalidAggressiveCPUPowerCorrectionExcep.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

InvalidDomainID.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed due to an Invalid Domain ID.
InvalidDomainID.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed due to an Invalid Domain ID. IPMI Error Code is %1.
InvalidDomainID.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

InvalidPolicyID.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed due to an Invalid Policy ID.
InvalidPolicyID.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed due to an Invalid Policy ID. IPMI Error Code is %1.
InvalidPolicyID.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

InvalidThresholdPowerLimit.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because either Number Threshold is too large or Power limit is invalid.
InvalidThresholdPowerLimit.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because either Number Threshold is too large or Power limit is invalid. IPMI Error Code is %1.
InvalidThresholdPowerLimit.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

NoLimitingPolicy.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because no Policy is currently Limiting for specified Domain ID.
NoLimitingPolicy.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because no Policy is currently Limiting for specified Domain ID. IPMI Error Code is %1.
NoLimitingPolicy.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

ParamNotSupportedinCurrentState.Description: Cannot execute command. Command, or request parameter(s), not supported in present state of Node Manager Service.
ParamNotSupportedinCurrentState.Message: The request could not be completed because a command or request parameter is not supported in the present state of Node Manager Service. IPMI Error Code is %1.
ParamNotSupportedinCurrentState.Resolution: Verify that the Host is in On Condition and the Node Manager Service is not in a conflicting state and resubmit the request.

ParameterOutOfRange.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Parameter is Out Of Range.
ParameterOutOfRange.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Parameter is Out Of Range. IPMI Error Code is %1.
ParameterOutOfRange.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

PolicyCreationFailed.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Policy in given power domain cannot be created in the current configuration.
PolicyCreationFailed.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Policy in given power domain cannot be created in the current configuration. IPMI Error Code is %1.
PolicyCreationFailed.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

PolicyTriggerLimitOutOfRange.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Policy Trigger Limit is Out of Range.
PolicyTriggerLimitOutOfRange.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Policy Trigger Limit is Out of Range. IPMI Error Code is %1.
PolicyTriggerLimitOutOfRange.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

PolicyUpdationFailed.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Policy could not be updated since policy ID already exist and one of it parameters, which is changing, is not modifiable when policy is enabled.
PolicyUpdationFailed.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Policy could not be updated since policy ID already exist and one of it parameters, which is changing, is not modifiable when policy is enabled. IPMI Error Code is %1.
PolicyUpdationFailed.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

PowerDomainNotSupported.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Power Domain is not supported for given Domain ID and Mode Configuration.
PowerDomainNotSupported.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Power Domain is not supported for given Domain ID and Mode Configuration. IPMI Error Code is %1.
PowerDomainNotSupported.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

PropertyValueError.Description: Indicates that a property doesn't have a proper value with respect to a related attribute.
PropertyValueError.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 must be %3 than the value %4 for the property %5.
PropertyValueError.Resolution: Make sure the attribute has a proper value with respect to a related attribute.

ServiceTemporarilyUnavailableDueToBMCBoo.Description: Indicates the Redfish Service is going to be temporarily unavailable since BMC Reboot is in Progress.
ServiceTemporarilyUnavailableDueToBMCBoo.Message: The Redfish Service is going to be temporarily unavailable since BMC Reboot is in Progress. Please issue further requests to the Redfish Service after some time.

StatisticReportingPeriodOutOfRange.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed because Statistic Reporting Period is Out of Range.
StatisticReportingPeriodOutOfRange.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed because Statistic Reporting Period is Out of Range. IPMI Error Code is %1.
StatisticReportingPeriodOutOfRange.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

Success.Description: Indicates that all conditions of a successful operation have been met.
Success.Message: The IPMI request was processed and completed successfully.

UnknownPolicyType.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed due to an Unknown Policy Type.
UnknownPolicyType.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed due to an Unknown Policy Type. IPMI Error Code is %1.
UnknownPolicyType.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

UnsupportedPolicyTrigger.Description: Indicates that the request could not be completed due to an Unsupported Policy Ttrigger.
UnsupportedPolicyTrigger.Message: The IPMI request could not be completed due to an Unsupported Policy Ttrigger. IPMI Error Code is %1.
UnsupportedPolicyTrigger.Resolution: Verify the parameters passed to the IPMI request and resubmit the request.

Name: Ami Node Manager Oem Message Registry
